olive oil
1 packet fusilli
½ bunch spring onion
1 stalk celery
1 carrot
2 packet diced bacon
1 sachet Tex-Mex spice blend
1 packet tomato paste
20 g butter
½ packet cream
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese

• Boil the kettle. Half-fill a large saucepan with boiling water and add a generous pinch of salt.
• Cook fusilli in boiling water, over high heat, until ‘al dente’, 12 minutes.
• Reserve some pasta water (1/2 cup for 2 people / 1 cup for 4 people). Drain, then return fusilli to saucepan with a drizzle of olive oil.

• While the pasta is cooking, thinly slice spring onion (see ingredients).
• Finely chop celery. Grate the carrot.

Little cooks: Under adult supervision, older kids can help grate the carrot.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook diced bacon and celery in batches until golden, 3-4 minutes. Return all bacon and celery to the pan.
• Add carrot and cook, tossing, until softened, 4-5 minutes.
• Add Tex-Mex spice blend, tomato paste and the butter and cook, stirring, until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Reduce the heat to medium, then add cream (see ingredients), chicken-style stock powder and the reserved pasta water. Stir to combine.
• Remove from heat, then add fusilli and half the shredded Cheddar cheese. Toss to combine.

• Divide Tex-Mex bacon and veggie fusilli between bowls.
• Top with remaining Cheddar cheese and sprinkle with spring onion to serve. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Add the finishing touch by sprinkling the cheese on top.